<br>
Also, the rules say a cold and magic resistance of at least 70 before buffed.  Can someone suggest some gear for an iskar shaman?  Hopefully without losing too much Wis.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><hr>
Zatriz Spiritscale<br>
Channeler of the Scaled Mystics<br>
Peacekeepers<br>
Karana chapter</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uhaemish.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Haemish</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>ezOP</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(3/19/01 1:47:03 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.godwin.com/sd/haemish.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Suggestions</span><hr size=1> Yes, a level 40 shaman is acceptable, we need all the healing classes we can get. Plus, even at level 40 a shaman brings some good buffs to the table, and can be used in the buffing line. Ask Brisos of Seekers of Knowledge about his role on the last Vox raid (and that cool staff he won). <br>
<br>
For a list of good cold and fire resist gear, check this thread:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsfrm8.showMessage?topicID=70.topic">pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncil...D=70.topic</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
It isn't a complete list, as it doesn't have a lot of the Velious stuff on it, but it is pretty good at getting the jewelry right. <br>
<br>
Haemish <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CBC6B1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uzatrizspiritscale.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zatriz Spiritscale</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(3/19/01 2:29:01 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Suggestions</span><hr size=1> Nice lists.... Going to drop my Wisdom an awful lot, but I assume that is normal.  Looks like I am in for some serious work to get some items, mostly because I just blew a lot of money getting my level 34 spells (a lot being almost 200pp to me <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ).<br>
<br>
How about DoT's?  Are they allowed now on the big raids? <p><hr>
Zatriz Spiritscale<br>
Channeler of the Scaled Mystics<br>
Peacekeepers<br>
Karana chapter</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uhaemish.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Haemish</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>ezOP</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(3/20/01 9:30:10 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.godwin.com/sd/haemish.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Suggestions</span><hr size=1> DOT's are allowed, but until a shaman reaches about level 46 or so, they are put in the healing line (and if we are short on healers, they go to healing as well). With the dragons being level 55, you'll be resisted a lot. With that in mind, healers can now worry about keeping their wisdom up. <br>
<br>
Haemish <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CBC6B1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uzatrizspiritscale.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zatriz Spiritscale</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(3/20/01 10:03:54 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Suggestions</span><hr size=1> Soa re you saying that the healers do not have to worry about sv Cold and Magic?  The way I read the recap on the last raid the healers were in another room and seemingly in not much danger.....<br>
<br>
I found some nice tailored Velious stuff for shaman, that has both Wis and svCold.  Still will probably pick that stuff up if I can (some of it is an upgrade to what I have). <p><hr>
Zatriz Spiritscale<br>
Channeler of the Scaled Mystics<br>
Peacekeepers<br>
Karana chapter</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/utildartreewalker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tildar Treewalker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(3/20/01 11:59:45 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.emeraldaxe.com/images/tildar.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Suggestions</span><hr size=1> Can this apply to a druid as well? I am figuring that I would be on a secondary healing line... at 43 I have some buffs... but realistically what could my role be? <p><A HREF="http://eq.guildmagic.com/character.cfm?ID=9288">Tildar Treewalker</A> <BR>
Druid of Tunare <BR>
Emerald Axe <BR>
<A HREF="http://www.emeraldaxe.com/tildar"> Tildar's Druid Pages <BR>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CBC6B1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uhaemish.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Haemish</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>ezOP</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(3/20/01 12:00:01 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.godwin.com/sd/haemish.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Suggestions</span><hr size=1> The healers don't have to worry about it as much, because they are usually far away from the dragon. But it's not a bad idea to have some, just in case. The lower level you are, the more you'll need it. Magic resist you need no matter what, because the fear has an immense range. <br>
<br>
Haemish <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uzatrizspiritscale.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zatriz Spiritscale</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(3/20/01 12:08:39 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Suggestions</span><hr size=1> Thanks Haemish.  That helps a lot and fills in a lot of the gaps I had.  So, if I am on the healing line magic resists are better to have.  But if I get into the fray, I need both for sure.<br>
<br>
Cool deal. <p><hr>
